body:
 Hi guys.
I am testing React Component

``` js
class NumericInput extends React.Component {

    onChange(event) {
        console.log('Trigger On Change');
        this.props.onChange(event.target.value);
    }
    onKeyDown(event) {
        if (event.keyCode === 13) {
             return; //Do nothing
        }
    }
    render() {
        return (
            <Input
                {...this.props}
                type='text'
                value={this.state.value}
                onChange={this.onChange.bind(this)}
                onKeyDown={this.onKeyDown.bind(this)}
            />
        );
    }
}
```

``` js
beforeEach(() => {
   onChange = jasmine.createSpy('onChange');
   NumericInput = rewire('../NumericInput');
   renderedNumericInput = TestUtils.renderIntoDocument(
       <NumericInput onChange={onChange}/>
   );
   inputNode = 
 React.findDOMNode(TestUtils.findRenderedDOMComponentWithTag(renderedNumericInput, 'input'));
});

it ('Should call onChange when user does not press ENTER key', () => {
    TestUtils.Simulate.keyDown(inputNode, {keyCode: 46});
    expect(onChange.calls.count()).toEqual(1);
});

```

By Default in View, when i type, the _onKeyDown_ is triggered and then _onChange_.
But in Unit Test it does not trigger _onChange_
